7q1l A 39 B 179

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between two units of Serotransferrin at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Serotransferrin at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

4x1d B 161 B 174

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Serotransferrin at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
